About:
“Cotton Candy Clouds” is a collaboration between Valntn, Sweater Beats, and Trevor Dering. The song was written, and produced by the three of them, and is sung by Trevor.
Here is what ‘Spinnin Records’, had to say about the song;
“Sweet sounds from Valntn, Sweater Beats and Trevor Dering, as they paint the sky with ‘Cotton Candy Clouds’. The record brings laidback beats, warm horns, organ chords, and sultry vocals and raps, giving it a catchy blend of jazz and soul with subtle, contemporary pop sounds.” – ‘Spinnin Records’

“Take Me Where your Heart Is” is the third single from Q’s first released EP titled, [The Shave Experiment] (
https://genius.com/albums/Q/The-shave-experiment
). This song takes listeners through a rollercoaster of emotions that explain exactly how love feels. Q expresses his longing for a specific someone, through catchy lyrics that describe the ups and downs of wanting love and wanting to be loved.
“Take Me Where Your Heart Is” was released on October 9th, 2020 in addition to the music video which was also released that same day. [Music Video] (
)
